<hr local-id=3D"6a802643-e38e-4da6-9d16-1d014cf38ca9">
<h2 local-id=3D"d379401a86a9" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-3.2Environments">3=
.2 Environments</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cc387513310e">For this implementation, a simplified environm=
ent strategy was adopted:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"ef5b8b0a-49d4-4137-bf33-45e1971d6b41">
<li local-id=3D"2f10b03d-3700-479e-a620-385cf04a273c">
<p local-id=3D"f19542870a48">Development: Local system for Docker build and=
 testing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1bc7074b-0bc9-455e-9120-a926e5975235">
<p local-id=3D"8c58b5fdbb17">Staging/Validation: AWS ECS and EC2 deployment=
s</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"34826526-5eab-4b8b-8294-6308ac9c9283">
<p local-id=3D"df752bcdaea9">Production Simulation: Publicly accessible end=
points via S3, ECS (ALB), and EC2</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"9669f26afccd">Each deployment model was independently valida=
ted through public endpoint testing.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"5f5b8a15-327c-4a51-874b-75e8cb134f87">
<h2 local-id=3D"ac380bae7253" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-3.4ApplicationArch=
itecture&amp;UserRequestFlow">3.4 Application Architecture &amp; User Reque=
st Flow</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"666131152943" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-ApplicationArchite=
ctureOverview">Application Architecture Overview</h3>
<p local-id=3D"5f160decbf61">The architecture supports three independent fr=
ontend hosting patterns:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d891970d-b5e0-4692-81a9-e765f4162237">
<li local-id=3D"8d970872-8c6a-444d-9626-4dd9d7d25c08">
<p local-id=3D"0c21c39f48ac">Static Hosting via S3</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f1570e32-5e83-43fa-b334-bdc009f7f6f4">
<p local-id=3D"11b1d8589766">Container Hosting via ECS + ALB</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a9249e4-d708-4b1e-8ae8-8c4078beeb15">
<p local-id=3D"574335ba4f9a">Server Hosting via EC2 + Nginx</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"fd1e425d279e">Each approach demonstrates different levels of=
 scalability, operational complexity, and cost structure.</p>
