<h2 local-id=3D"cfb2f6f4285b" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-4.DevelopmentPract=
ices">4. Development Practices</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b62054a9e507">This section describes the development practic=
es followed during the implementation of the DevOps project, focusing on co=
de management, integration workflow, testing approach, and quality controls=
 adopted during the internship engagement.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"1c428f8c-58a4-4d0e-935c-b0431a91b3c2">
<h3 local-id=3D"35440a3b633b" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-4.1VersionControl"=
>4.1 Version Control</h3>
<p local-id=3D"33fb92dfe699">Version control was managed using <strong>Git<=
/strong> to track source code changes and maintain consistency across deplo=
yments.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"88a412fa-37c7-45db-a3bf-7531fdd1ac2d">
<li local-id=3D"b1bd46fa-46a9-4fc9-9cc9-bea94a56b2dc">
<p local-id=3D"e0592851fdbd">Source code for all frontend applications was =
maintained in Git repositories.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"06bb6f56-2e7b-428c-9d57-decc64da8b41">
<p local-id=3D"5014887db61e">Logical separation of projects was followed (S=
3 static app, ECS containerized apps, EC2-hosted app).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7702a0e2-d9c7-40e1-b861-687dff790969">
<p local-id=3D"552109368980">Commits were made incrementally to reflect mea=
ningful changes such as UI updates, configuration changes, and deployment r=
eadiness.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"74344ffe-e43c-4598-a483-0097e9e88dac">
<p local-id=3D"64ae62f5b8d3">Git was primarily used for source tracking and=
 recovery rather than complex branching strategies, considering the scope a=
nd duration of the project.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"d90dfd0d3f71">This ensured traceability of changes and simpl=
ified collaboration and rollback if required.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f73763f9-1b06-4d5f-a60a-a6d3034149f6">
<h3 local-id=3D"1e843ffb0351" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-4.2ContinuousInteg=
ration">4.2 Continuous Integration</h3>
<p local-id=3D"13351852148a">A lightweight continuous integration approach =
was followed due to the frontend-focused nature of the project.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"93d1ef9c-0b64-4597-94e7-ce1c8651995b">
<li local-id=3D"a3bb1be4-7f78-4e89-9fdc-1f546abbb0c8">
<p local-id=3D"5434bf74b5a2">Code was validated locally before deployment.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bef78428-92e4-4a42-8c80-c4d11dd5ac98">
<p local-id=3D"08a214f4c3cd">Docker images were built locally and pushed to=
 <strong>Amazon ECR</strong> after successful validation.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9b39655f-8bf7-42dd-bd56-535b17680640">
<p local-id=3D"408fe232e41b">For ECS-based deployments, updated Docker imag=
es automatically triggered new task revisions during service updates.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"4d63730a-e512-4358-abbe-072b8d196db1">
<p local-id=3D"53cc7e6b948d">Manual validation acted as a CI checkpoint bef=
ore deployment to AWS services.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e179cc8f7c48">Although a full CI toolchain (e.g., Jenkins/Gi=
tHub Actions) was not implemented, the process ensured stable and deployabl=
e builds.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9fcaadd8-75f1-44ec-b7dc-46af880a3fbb">
<h3 local-id=3D"84c88423ebee" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-4.3AutomatedTestin=
g">4.3 Automated Testing</h3>
<p local-id=3D"058dfd132be8">Formal automated testing frameworks were not i=
ntegrated due to project scope constraints; however, basic validation steps=
 were followed:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"63f4fca1-b45e-4517-b69b-47ea3c6b74cf">
<li local-id=3D"674cc43b-5abb-4960-be16-b9f683cd7d08">
<p local-id=3D"5897e542199c">Frontend functionality was manually tested in =
local browsers before deployment.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5e9d6446-34aa-4919-af4d-72a40c50560d">
<p local-id=3D"48456ee888de">Post-deployment testing was performed using pu=
blic endpoints (S3 URL, ALB DNS, EC2 public IP).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"32c9af20-9da8-453e-b639-8dfa6f66b22c">
<p local-id=3D"f0ec3044f848">Application behavior such as page load, UI ren=
dering, and API responses (for the air quality application) was verified.</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e636619ffe84">This ensured functional correctness of applica=
tions across all hosting models.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f4cf56f6-1362-4066-9624-00ee673192a9">
<h3 local-id=3D"0043ff3166ec" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-4.4CodeQualityandA=
nalysis">4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</h3>
<p local-id=3D"622bce93b9d6">Basic code quality practices were followed to =
maintain readability and maintainability:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"7ea08e57-ea59-43e4-8827-396ac5bad5e6">
<li local-id=3D"b8739115-f214-4437-a8f8-7a7c345453b8">
<p local-id=3D"558c1772206c">Clean folder structure for frontend assets (HT=
ML, CSS, JavaScript).</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8e2e52f2-cf9f-470e-90e8-b1938cc05e12">
<p local-id=3D"c6c80556f001">Removal of default server files (e.g., Nginx d=
efault index page) before deployment.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"270a7687-ace2-4082-87c5-51eddaf8bf85">
<p local-id=3D"23602a3fced8">Consistent naming conventions for files, Docke=
r images, ECS tasks, and services.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5724a3d1-0547-4460-a38a-6fb8801237f9">
<p local-id=3D"1158cfe425b1">Configuration values were externalized where a=
pplicable to simplify updates.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3c1b81727fbe">Given the frontend-centric and demonstrative n=
ature of the project, lightweight quality controls were sufficient and appr=
opriate.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"64bac5927d9e" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-5.1DeploymentStrat=
egy">5.1 Deployment Strategy</h2>
<p local-id=3D"c3bfe2c2ab10">Three independent deployment strategies were i=
mplemented to demonstrate different hosting models within AWS:</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"ce653d124102" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-1.StaticDeployment=
(AmazonS3)">1. Static Deployment (Amazon S3)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"aa86e111-3c23-4a39-af60-27a21d948685">
<li local-id=3D"0bda352b-0477-47f8-87d4-4facfb47dbca">
<p local-id=3D"2d6951adb442">Frontend files (HTML, CSS, JS) were uploaded d=
irectly to S3 buckets.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5e9bfcf-688d-4258-939b-a63e377e9455">
<p local-id=3D"089885057523">Static website hosting was enabled.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d98d1050-10bc-4622-b26a-adb72d68aa3d">
<p local-id=3D"78bd4e4debb2">Public access was configured using bucket poli=
cies.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cd12b05d-34af-42c1-9a04-d54a06791594">
<p local-id=3D"6fba9c9037d8">Deployment involved uploading updated files to=
 the bucket.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"4a59951aa0a6">This approach is cost-effective and suitable f=
or fully static applications.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"d2959bb8-71a2-4122-b924-fa06af931166">
<h3 local-id=3D"2463e1cf8bbd" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-2.ContainerizedDep=
loyment(AmazonECS=E2=80=93Fargate)">2. Containerized Deployment (Amazon ECS=
 =E2=80=93 Fargate)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"1848b668-4e36-4869-a58b-84949f0640df">
<li local-id=3D"3d52b537-9964-4a12-8379-8ce260600f7b">
<p local-id=3D"d51a2c359b47">Frontend applications were containerized using=
 Docker.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8d658e53-e939-40fb-90da-de45c43558f2">
<p local-id=3D"79ce9a95fa60">Docker images were pushed to Amazon ECR.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"27f2ea3c-3ce3-40e2-9cd6-936b1d6197db">
<p local-id=3D"c22c6fd1916a">ECS Task Definitions referenced ECR images.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"1c30249c-c951-4a61-8020-13f2161993e0">
<p local-id=3D"fd8f10aab34e">ECS Services maintained the desired task count=
.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7bd50ab8-0d8d-4877-8685-85bc6951fa1d">
<p local-id=3D"040d731fca2d">Application Load Balancer (ALB) routed HTTP tr=
affic to running tasks.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c3b22e47d5a7">Service updates were performed by pushing a ne=
w Docker image and updating the ECS service to use the latest task revision=
.</p>
<p local-id=3D"54fdc0778210">This strategy provides scalability, isolation,=
 and operational flexibility.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"3dd7913f-ac23-4d16-af33-fa35a8fcbbe9">
<h3 local-id=3D"410414995bd2" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-3.Server-BasedDepl=
oyment(AmazonEC2+Nginx)">3. Server-Based Deployment (Amazon EC2 + Nginx)</h=
3>
<ul local-id=3D"1c203e71-8936-4b07-8b01-911ae069ef84">
<li local-id=3D"50aa9359-266e-4de5-90df-75105b7e9aec">
<p local-id=3D"a401063d78c0">EC2 instance (t3.micro) was provisioned.</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"c392591e-545c-4ed4-b366-1ba61d8a0376">
<p local-id=3D"774275799931">Nginx was installed and configured as the web =
server.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0ccae7fe-2315-489e-b6b2-4b45ed7225f0">
<p local-id=3D"b8b5321e73bd">Application files were manually deployed to <c=
ode>/usr/share/nginx/html</code>.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb882e0f-04a7-4000-a2d9-5941878227fb">
<p local-id=3D"96584cca0839">Security groups were configured to allow HTTP =
(80) and SSH (22).</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"88a0ff023b50">Deployment updates required SSH access and fil=
e replacement followed by Nginx restart.</p>
<p local-id=3D"991d684734ea">This approach represents traditional VM-based =
hosting.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"193f8ecd-f566-4987-9916-7c0242ec47f5">
<h2 local-id=3D"eaa7bdc793a8" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-5.2ConfigurationMa=
nagement">5.2 Configuration Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bf7dcadc2987">Configuration management was handled using AWS=
-native settings and structured deployment practices:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8a9f5ca5-4b3d-4b07-b9e6-6b6c549f6432">
<li local-id=3D"dd8870aa-7170-4a6d-b642-2eb5a8a375f7">
<p local-id=3D"b7c8f80e6456"><strong>Infrastructure Configuration</strong><=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"81364b2c-2a44-42a3-b44b-55cc85ba028b">
<li local-id=3D"ab432572-d025-4606-92db-4c6437a451b6">
<p local-id=3D"6ce6a9eb28a7">ECS Task Definitions defined CPU, memory, and =
container image.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a657ce46-8c39-42e0-b6fd-34f0c11ab61c">
<p local-id=3D"033fb4bbb32a">Security Groups defined network access rules.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"328ac03e-bc10-4503-a139-bd15bc06b1e8">
<p local-id=3D"4cdbb73f024c">ALB target groups controlled routing behavior.=
</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"8b56411f-6ffa-41a5-be46-348f18e4e247">
<p local-id=3D"97d369b781c1"><strong>Application Configuration</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"00b2911e-d681-4f62-a6ea-325f6fd19111">
<li local-id=3D"8e2ca44f-8101-477c-8d59-e8353aecd38f">
<p local-id=3D"90edd89a86c1">Static frontend files structured consistently.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"cdc766fe-c038-408b-9a20-108a90c5158c">
<p local-id=3D"fbad4049ab9c">Dockerfile defined build instructions for cont=
ainerized apps.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"807ba7da-6a74-4a43-9f1c-bcb5746a517d">
<p local-id=3D"15938357956c">Nginx default configuration used for EC2 hosti=
ng.</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"5171b8f2cab6">Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools were not im=
plemented due to project scope constraints. Configuration was performed via=
 AWS Console and CLI for validation purposes.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"5c45ab03-3c1b-46fb-a8d9-eebaad23b7dc">
<h2 local-id=3D"044cdf891b60" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-5.3ContinuousDeliv=
ery/Deployment">5.3 Continuous Delivery / Deployment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"259c1f820325">A simplified continuous deployment workflow wa=
s followed:</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"c8ba120d6361" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-S3DeploymentFlow:"=
>S3 Deployment Flow:</h3>
<p local-id=3D"ec1c7a99e625">Local Update =E2=86=92 Upload to S3 =E2=86=92 =
Immediate Public Availability</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"a4f0abcc5b95" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-ECSDeploymentFlow:=
">ECS Deployment Flow:</h3>
<p local-id=3D"0aefda1eb343">Local Code Update =E2=86=92 Docker Build =E2=
=86=92 Push to ECR =E2=86=92 Update ECS Service =E2=86=92 Rolling Task Repl=
acement</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"f90ecaad53b8" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-EC2DeploymentFlow:=
">EC2 Deployment Flow:</h3>
<p local-id=3D"1556c73f6387">SSH into Instance =E2=86=92 Replace Files =E2=
=86=92 Restart Nginx =E2=86=92 Validate via Public IP</p>
<p local-id=3D"71b1fa93c304">Deployment validation was performed after ever=
y release by accessing:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6ac0f76c-5ee4-47f9-8c6f-6ddb00dc0f71">
<li local-id=3D"4eebf40c-4550-4be2-9389-4c6c0e32125c">
<p local-id=3D"52aa2c52ffdb">S3 Website Endpoint</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f97716a7-9acf-42da-8985-6c11edbb3171">
<p local-id=3D"e10ee3680a95">ALB DNS Endpoint</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"90e0514a-e6e0-4fa2-b1ae-86a0ce2d039a">
<p local-id=3D"98b516a487cd">EC2 Public IP</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"e6ef5c41eef4">Each release was manually verified to ensure a=
pplication availability and correctness.</p>
<h1 local-id=3D"c6a589e14630" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-6.MonitoringandInc=
identManagement">6. Monitoring and Incident Management</h1>
<p local-id=3D"61ffd4094313">This section describes the monitoring mechanis=
ms, alerting structure, and incident handling approach implemented for the =
frontend deployment across S3, ECS, and EC2.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"6f838e1f-6493-4173-b006-a34314dc796d">
<h2 local-id=3D"847da51df29a" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-6.1MonitoringTools=
andMetrics">6.1 Monitoring Tools and Metrics</h2>
<p local-id=3D"524e1edfa66c">Monitoring was implemented using AWS native se=
rvice visibility and built-in health checks.</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"cac47e454bbc" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-AmazonECSMonitorin=
g">Amazon ECS Monitoring</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"82595004-a571-4678-8b7a-c167a61882e4">
<li local-id=3D"f8acc4f7-654e-46d9-88f2-e887bde8bdf0">
<p local-id=3D"cea4f78cb4aa">ECS Service dashboard used to monitor:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"46137e91-3bec-486f-8897-15190543c77e">
<li local-id=3D"c6802646-8ca1-4d8f-a282-3aa5dacedc07">
<p local-id=3D"e81befaafe4f">Running task count</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"45398d3e-6321-4338-89bc-185c186333ad">
<p local-id=3D"2ec5bb356569">Desired vs Running tasks</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5693e562-e5f6-41a9-b4d7-b66d183de3bb">
<p local-id=3D"a0dee2157c19">Task health status</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"cbfe7843-65d8-41f3-bde6-533258884c7c">
<p local-id=3D"6cca012d4212">Application Load Balancer health checks valida=
ted container availability.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b7cbd1fd-cb7e-442c-9cc1-6ac91f583d45">
<p local-id=3D"04b912534981">ECS automatically replaced unhealthy tasks.</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3f426431b17c"><strong>Key Metrics Observed:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"87ee7ea3-5303-451d-a4fd-23cb4d2b534e">
<li local-id=3D"0f34677a-3f92-4eee-a95e-c68fe0caf180">
<p local-id=3D"750a61eaf4f0">Task health status</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1ca4e3b9-7a5a-4f58-afbb-2d4ab58bb838">
<p local-id=3D"238d55cc71c9">Service stability</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27ab3f7c-c5e2-4f0b-82bb-8beae79812e9">
<p local-id=3D"fc62b5454ab4">Load balancer target health</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"19561882-3c67-49cc-b99f-ae4bbc13f86a">
<h3 local-id=3D"f67c0d0ae209" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-AmazonEC2Monitorin=
g">Amazon EC2 Monitoring</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"757a6332-5703-4cd9-a094-d1540ea8bcf9">
<li local-id=3D"ef48afcf-9e2a-47f0-a396-8cdd0c500735">
<p local-id=3D"b15e3e9813db">EC2 Instance Status Checks:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"02c6697d-80fe-47fa-b968-9ff3a93a9651">
<li local-id=3D"33b22292-2dfe-4f6d-8090-3f834637f00e">
<p local-id=3D"ef09de44a8ad">System status checks</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8b834414-f28a-4e67-84dd-b7ebd815b49a">
<p local-id=3D"90c69e9a27dd">Instance status checks</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"6a4072ee-2715-476c-ba65-779d516a1f6e">
<p local-id=3D"fa6ab13d501a">Nginx service status verified via terminal.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"e8cc7811-1912-4fc4-825b-131f870e6187">
<p local-id=3D"39136aec7b7d">Public endpoint validation used to confirm ser=
vice availability.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"394157accb93"><strong>Key Metrics Observed:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"ac7677a2-505f-47e3-8c09-0be5794dff87">
<li local-id=3D"21e85fab-65fa-4392-8707-8d1c7311094b">
<p local-id=3D"d03b17efe636">Instance running state</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1796a6be-3b0e-4d95-be4b-e7fa9d647630">
<p local-id=3D"b927f2b1bcfa">CPU utilization (basic monitoring)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6c2d5f29-f4cb-4854-88f6-e7d09127b8a6">
<p local-id=3D"4c638bed2e10">Network accessibility via HTTP (Port 80)</p></=
li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"8586c723-584f-43f1-97d2-988cf91c0751">
<h3 local-id=3D"193085c74fb1" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-AmazonS3Monitoring=
">Amazon S3 Monitoring</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"5b2131d8-0a91-4a15-83bd-e8cf417462fb">
<li local-id=3D"85e3b2e9-1c15-445b-befe-8f8e69303be0">
<p local-id=3D"fbd9f9c17ee7">S3 bucket object availability verified through=
 website endpoint testing.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"829c1e99-789d-4f2d-8cb0-8da3da28038b">
<p local-id=3D"f678984189bb">Static website hosting functionality validated=
 manually.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ef0251a9-2b2e-4679-8463-a89b1944a8fb">
<p local-id=3D"26cc184ca8ea">No advanced logging or CloudWatch metrics were=
 configured due to project scope.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"5b38ddc9-eae8-48f2-9d83-3c95699007ac">
<h2 local-id=3D"ac64d306782a" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-6.2AlertingandNoti=
fication">6.2 Alerting and Notification</h2>
<p local-id=3D"fca424d02c74">Automated alerting mechanisms were not configu=
red in this implementation due to scope limitations. However:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"f00a1f44-e9ed-48a7-b9de-4f8ef0562fa9">
<li local-id=3D"826d1af2-21fa-4acc-88de-793a589d9b6a">
<p local-id=3D"ac792664d3a4">ECS automatically replaces failed containers.<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"31ac312e-c5f5-4175-b344-4f272455d99e">
<p local-id=3D"156a2ce4d34b">EC2 status checks detect infrastructure-level =
failures.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7108830a-9b45-496e-9bce-ba2990ee3202">
<p local-id=3D"ba197653ee47">ALB health checks ensure traffic is routed onl=
y to healthy targets.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"41f994ac5ae0">In production environments, integration with:<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"3a3cf7ee-6feb-4753-a888-a780251b9486">
<li local-id=3D"2f7f5388-ede3-4ff5-911f-44efaf0c3e28">
<p local-id=3D"fb85d8c171e2">Amazon CloudWatch Alarms</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"23cacf6c-1013-41f3-b547-a4faa6ea49c0">
<p local-id=3D"112849335f75">SNS Notifications</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"eb71c0c8-135b-40f0-b25d-a797cf44c842">
<p local-id=3D"fabe25dad84d">Centralized logging systems</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c1e1a54ecefd">would be recommended.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"72eaa390-df24-47d0-b114-0160c518451f">
<h2 local-id=3D"29f22dc67332" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-6.3IncidentManagem=
ent">6.3 Incident Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"71761a86e3ac">A simplified incident response approach was fo=
llowed:</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"2a986d5ddcc8" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-IncidentTypesIdent=
ified">Incident Types Identified</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"cd9c2f20-9245-47be-a6be-cb39b955d458">
<li local-id=3D"2985b5f9-c7d3-45ae-a8d0-3de20d823213">
<p local-id=3D"e62c727c08da">Application not loading</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"53ffcab3-e516-46f3-a2e0-1b501a029f42">
<p local-id=3D"34e429644ce3">ECS task failure</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1461b03e-d6b8-4f0b-8156-a54e484f84ec">
<p local-id=3D"44b950088f3c">EC2 service failure</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2b773330-c9ef-43e6-95d1-7c09587db897">
<p local-id=3D"50698537bfe9">Incorrect S3 configuration</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"ca404fe02983" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-ResolutionApproach=
">Resolution Approach</h3>
<p local-id=3D"fcde7d36beff"><strong>For ECS:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"1dd8cfd3-63b7-4d32-81f6-82d9a34535ab">
<li local-id=3D"9747e6fa-abe5-46a7-ba27-fe1dddd8cef0">
<p local-id=3D"0a6a36c0c4c0">Check ECS service dashboard.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"320912d5-1b72-43be-9867-939233c505b9">
<p local-id=3D"a28b0e26a92f">Verify running task count.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"16af98ef-361c-47d2-98b6-8c944c035522">
<p local-id=3D"b68c0a400b86">Validate target group health.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a299462b-ebe6-40dc-b77b-a65eb4996d10">
<p local-id=3D"007f63b7b073">Redeploy updated task definition if required.<=
/p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"d75cd8929f0c"><strong>For EC2:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"1406d92b-69b1-4942-ae7a-c3c0f2c6ce85">
<li local-id=3D"69570a02-7ca1-47dc-9e7a-b73a74716e71">
<p local-id=3D"b340343a4970">SSH into instance.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5d32d56b-f928-4046-b469-65ce3338b807">
<p local-id=3D"d09d7c49befe">Check Nginx service status.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"feb023be-88e6-4a82-8e3a-fe5ed79dc163">
<p local-id=3D"ff7f2850e5c6">Restart Nginx if required.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ac6f39ec-d883-4849-8057-defdd886083c">
<p local-id=3D"312bb66e44e9">Verify security group rules.</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"4e6816a269bb"><strong>For S3:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"e0a9100b-12e6-42da-ad07-7ab8054b82cb">
<li local-id=3D"ee635687-c97f-43f3-8df7-4680409659f4">
<p local-id=3D"ad3496e5b077">Verify bucket policy.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2861e4e1-3301-48ca-ab09-9328003320e9">
<p local-id=3D"190282608e1c">Confirm static hosting is enabled.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"58dadbaf-e477-47ef-beeb-8417fba36775">
<p local-id=3D"94822b9e8936">Validate object placement at root level.</p></=
li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"58fb46a9-b86b-458b-81ae-d969bfd62a23">
<h3 local-id=3D"d893712b2e01" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-OperationalRespons=
ibilityModel">Operational Responsibility Model</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"760" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"15=
c5b204-a3bd-4c16-a9fa-1a4452a5d4c7" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"529ecc1d-ac2b-4f0d-94c5-20f930e56985">
<th data-local-id=3D"0c317c7b-3462-4747-8553-eb871b8b8c8d" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"3f9baab7965f">Component</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e4b18bd6-1890-40b0-936f-8f86b66ab16f" class=3D"conflue=
nceTh">
<p local-id=3D"18b9b8e0595e">Responsibility</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4ee0eb0c-f049-48a8-8e03-0304ea1a2eeb">
