<p local-id=3D"4bbdeae2f3ae"></p>
<h1 local-id=3D"ce0ee78cb7e6" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-7.Security&amp;Com=
pliance">7. Security &amp; Compliance</h1>
<p local-id=3D"b8da44babdbd">Security was implemented using AWS-native cont=
rols to ensure controlled access, network isolation, and proper permission =
management across S3, ECS, and EC2 deployments.</p>
<p local-id=3D"c489361152f6">The implementation follows the principle of le=
ast privilege and basic cloud security best practices suitable for frontend=
 application hosting.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"785b3f93-7d9a-4257-8031-57f4dce2e7fd">
<h2 local-id=3D"4b2fab6030ab" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-7.1InfrastructureS=
ecurity">7.1 Infrastructure Security</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"78e810bdb5a2" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-NetworkSecurity(Se=
curityGroups)">Network Security (Security Groups)</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"2c5eb25b-006e-4c3f-bc2e-dd49caebbd0d">
<li local-id=3D"2b6b6b87-68b7-4356-b2c5-078e49353f85">
<p local-id=3D"47bd71fe2cbc">EC2 Security Groups were configured to allow:<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"c55d623b-7ef6-4e5f-b349-5d68cc556926">
<li local-id=3D"0596db75-d600-4e8e-b4d2-3019fb4e8b34">
<p local-id=3D"9360465dfedd">HTTP (Port 80) for public access</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"4a01742f-657a-4220-a82b-8c226244af7f">
<p local-id=3D"7125af35cc86">SSH (Port 22) for administrative access</p></l=
i>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"05422969-2eb8-4f71-a816-c3af336f81ae">
<p local-id=3D"a7f9b1115a1b">ECS Services were associated with security gro=
ups allowing controlled inbound traffic from the Application Load Balancer.=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"33fe8102-0b20-495a-b881-b498833f6e35">
<p local-id=3D"c9117df42570">ALB was configured as internet-facing with HTT=
P routing to ECS tasks.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"abde97f1de8d">This ensures that traffic is routed only throu=
gh defined entry points.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9e58a202-afbb-4593-94f6-0493cd5f0087">
<h3 local-id=3D"7649df7340a9" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-ApplicationLoadBal=
ancerSecurity">Application Load Balancer Security</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"b5c3fed7-99db-415d-94fb-148a203c7363">
<li local-id=3D"4b284a95-e86c-4536-8357-e6ba7579bac9">
<p local-id=3D"a46357700a4e">ALB distributes traffic only to healthy ECS ta=
rgets.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"be177976-d1a3-42f3-9f65-68b46feae6de">
<p local-id=3D"c6b5d180520b">Target groups ensure traffic is routed only to=
 validated container instances.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"799a5685-da9d-443f-9922-c28fec557c91">
<p local-id=3D"3b79f22955f0">Direct access to container tasks is restricted=
.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bfe5ffdace72">This prevents exposure of backend container en=
dpoints directly to the internet.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"486c1178-e5f1-4871-a2da-e4bc0c205e5d">
<h3 local-id=3D"4d3c9fc887a4" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-S3SecurityControls=
">S3 Security Controls</h3>
<ul local-id=3D"c2066e54-8bb8-4630-8e98-0add3d0ad2ab">
<li local-id=3D"c010eea7-ddc2-426b-b313-041d3464b2a4">
<p local-id=3D"b4b8cd0e33bb">S3 buckets were configured with:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d3240296-11f8-413f-ac09-f9e91a3828bf">
<li local-id=3D"1688c826-e88e-4c17-8d92-69c4f2320075">
<p local-id=3D"901d21c58a18">Static website hosting enabled</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5a2b180a-9eee-47e5-be7d-31842caa6d98">
<p local-id=3D"09e773d0cdba">Explicit bucket policy granting public read ac=
cess to objects</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"365694d0-7fe8-4029-864f-9cdf8f85c017">
<p local-id=3D"4a74eba291c7">No write permissions were granted publicly.</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"5f731ad8-91cc-41e2-adf7-25ab442ea22e">
<p local-id=3D"56bf54f71287">Bucket-level configuration ensures only static=
 assets are accessible.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ecfc2b877a8e">Public access was intentionally restricted to =
object read-only operations for hosting purposes.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"4c8078a6-2782-4bb4-8b61-3acaf5df3d7c">
<h2 local-id=3D"636111d42129" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-7.2IdentityandAcce=
ssManagement(IAM)">7.2 Identity and Access Management (IAM)</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"180d8117-83f0-4bb6-a8eb-189cc7173602">
<li local-id=3D"a7dd33c3-ffb9-41f9-b9c0-c35b3e146373">
<p local-id=3D"fcbb1f2bd590">AWS IAM users were used to configure AWS CLI a=
ccess.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a173f515-653c-4d65-9f48-b360ccfa8b4d">
<p local-id=3D"8dede8011dd8">ECR authentication required valid AWS credenti=
als before Docker image push.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"abedac2d-3dc1-43ee-9913-6dc902554197">
<p local-id=3D"579b08e2ad6f">ECS task execution roles allowed container run=
time access to required services.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d4edab64-fbb6-4591-bdd6-7a271abb2120">
<p local-id=3D"2382ce5b2f2c">No hardcoded credentials were stored inside ap=
plication files.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"3c9acd553063">Access to infrastructure components was contro=
lled via AWS IAM policies.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"f8525b05-ca37-4cba-aa31-9ef86552b227">
<h2 local-id=3D"88051ee324b2" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-7.3ContainerSecuri=
ty">7.3 Container Security</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"daa3a681-617e-4b93-b37f-833e8ab6ae5e">
<li local-id=3D"d3bb3afe-8834-4a12-b871-ba54309b6a82">
<p local-id=3D"58c5c06e1169">Docker images were stored in private Amazon EC=
R repositories.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"5b0f9f93-0ba6-47fb-9c30-63c3a370243e">
<p local-id=3D"5e1b3cdc0335">Only authenticated AWS users were allowed to p=
ush images.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9a1a7622-3f74-435b-b5e3-bc9e14857322">
<p local-id=3D"781bcc8f478f">ECS tasks used Fargate (serverless), eliminati=
ng host OS exposure.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"72b5e81f-9627-475e-af06-b78bfc2dfb15">
<p local-id=3D"bd8d092bdc9c">Containers were isolated per task definition.<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"af3e35961c60">This reduces attack surface compared to unmana=
ged container environments.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"0db1b1dd-5a66-43cb-813e-df81eefffd06">
<h2 local-id=3D"2b09f6c0cd2d" id=3D"T4-TechnicalDocument-7.4ComplianceConsi=
derations">7.4 Compliance Considerations</h2>
<p local-id=3D"f2d87380555d">Although this project was not bound to specifi=
c regulatory standards, the following best practices were followed:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"23468b48-8bfc-46bb-b329-3580f477b657">
<li local-id=3D"ffcc95cd-110e-49e5-9c7f-b0c3757ce137">
<p local-id=3D"e9a7b89a570a">No sensitive data stored in frontend code.</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"617c9869-2d5d-4072-b5b9-daf4bb765ed8">
<p local-id=3D"d790a9020cb1">IAM credentials managed securely.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c66b5a6e-e62f-4582-ae0b-979dede746b6">
<p local-id=3D"39b2160115a2">Public access explicitly configured and docume=
nted.</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"06fc82f5-dd1d-4ed5-88ed-0b360cd2dcbf">
<p local-id=3D"a478660284dd">Services deployed within AWS-managed infrastru=
cture.</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"dec109f4d4c1"></p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wr=
apper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"c=
onfluence-embedded-image image-center" alt=3D"image-20260219-170610.png" wi=
dth=3D"468" loading=3D"lazy" src=3D"7f32028ba92065aafc797ea369d76c80d9ba7af=
6927a4f42fbd5b61dff5d96c2" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/w=
iki/download/attachments/1787822142/image-20260219-170610.png?version=3D1&a=
mp;modificationDate=3D1771520781673&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data=
-height=3D"654" data-width=3D"1598" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" dat=
a-linked-resource-id=3D"1786970279" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data=
-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"=
image-20260219-170610.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wi=
ki" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-co=
ntainer-id=3D"1787822142" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"3" data=
